<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870731-0018 </DOCNO><HL> TRW Units ReceiveU.S. Defense WorkTotaling $777 Million</HL><DD> 07/31/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> ROK TRW LK MD VRO ITT RTNAEROSPACE (ARO)DEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF) </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Units of TRW Inc. were awarded $777 million in contracts for five early-warning satellites and development of a space surveillance and tracking system.    The satellites are used to watch for any missile launches from the Soviet Union. The contract, which is expected to be completed in March 1993, also includes launch support services for the satellites.    Raytheon Co. received contracts totaling $240.8 million to develop Standard missile improvements for the Navy and produce Patriot missile equipment for the Army.    The joint venture of ITT Corp. and Varo Inc. got Army contracts totaling $109.4 million for night-vision equipment.    McDonnell Douglas Astronautics Co., a unit of McDonnell Douglas Corp., was issued a $46.7 million Navy contract for Harpoon missile command and launch equipment.    Lockheed Corp. received a $32.1 million Air Force contract for development of a space surveillance and tracking system.    Rockwell International Corp. won Air Force contracts totaling $25 million for B1B aircraft engineering services. </TEXT></DOC>